1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 e6 4. Nf3 d5 5. Bb5 Nf6 6. d3 Be7 7. O-O Bd7 8. e5 $5
Ng8 (8... Ng4) 9. f5 $1 {This move is made possible, tactically, by the fact
that Black's d-pawn is hanging after he captures.} exf5 10. Nxd5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5
$6 (11. Bf4 $1 Nxf3+ (11... Bxb5 12. Bxe5 Qxd5 13. Bxg7 Bf6 14. c4 Qd7 15. Qe1+
Qe6 16. Bxh8 Bxh8 17. Qh4 Ne7 18. Rae1 Qf6 19. Qxh7 $18) 12. Qxf3 Bxb5 13. Nc7+
Kf8 14. Nxb5 $14) 11... Bxb5 12. c4 Bd7 13. Bf4 (13. Qb3 b6 14. Bf4 Nf6 15.
Nxe7 Qxe7 16. Nxd7 Qxd7 17. Rae1+ Kd8 18. Be5 $14) 13... Be6 (13... Nf6 14.
Nxe7 Qxe7 15. Qb3 $14) 14. Qa4+ Kf8 15. Nc7 Qd4+ 16. Kh1 Rd8 17. Qxa7 Bf6 18.
Rae1 Ne7 19. Qxb7 {White dines on the Black queenside, secure in the knowledge
that this will win any endgame that might ensue.} Bc8 20. Qb6 Ng6 21. Nc6 Qxd3
22. Nxd8 Nxf4 23. Re8# 1-0

