1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 g6 3. f4 Bg7 4. Nf3 d6 5. Bb5+ Bd7 {If Black plays here
instead of putting a Knight in the way, White should trade -- immediately.} 6.
Bxd7+ Nxd7 7. O-O Ngf6 8. d3 O-O 9. Qe1 Re8 10. Qh4 Rc8 11. f5 $1 Nh5 (11...
gxf5 12. Bh6 Bxh6 13. Qxh6 Qb6 14. Nh4 $1 e6 15. Rxf5 $1 exf5 16. Nxf5 Nh5 17.
Qxh5 Kh8 18. Qxf7 Rg8 19. Rb1 $18) 12. g4 Bf6 13. Bg5 $1 Bxg5 14. Nxg5 Nhf6 15.
fxg6 fxg6 16. Ne6 $1 Qb6 17. Qh6 Kf7 18. Ng5+ $1 Kg8 19. Nxh7 {One of two good
ways to win.} (19. Rxf6 $1 Nxf6 20. Nd5 $1 Qxb2 21. Nxf6+ Qxf6 22. Qxh7+ Kf8
23. Rf1 $1 {and White mates shortly.}) 19... Qxb2 (19... Nxh7 20. Qxg6+ Kh8 21.
Rf7 Ndf6 22. Qg7#) 20. Qxg6+ Kh8 21. Ng5 (21. Nxf6 Nxf6 22. Rf3 Qxa1+ 23. Kg2 {
and Black rapidly runs out of checks and gets mated.}) 21... Ne5 22. Qh6+ Kg8
23. Nd5 $1 Qd4+ 24. Kh1 Nexg4 25. Qg6+ {It's mate next move.} 1-0

