O-O 9. Qe1 Rb8 10. f5 d6 11. Qh4 e6 {This is a common defensive reaction to
White's Qh4/f5 attacking scheme. Perelshteyn's reaction is excellent and
instructive.} 12. fxg6 fxg6 (12... hxg6 {loses a piece to} 13. Bg5 $1 Rxb2 14.
