1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. g3 f5 4. Bg2 Nf6 5. d3 Bb4 6. e3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 d6 8. Rb1
O-O 9. Ne2 e4 10. d4 Na5 11. Qa4 c5 {[%csl Ga5][%cal Gd8a5] A nice touch,
defending the Knight with the Queen. Note that this would not have been
possible if Black's Queen were already on e8. Then again, in that case, Qa4
would not have been playable for White in the first place.} 12. O-O Be6 13. d5
